# System packages required by Manim Community Edition.
# Render reads this file during the build phase and installs each
# package via apt-get on top of the base Python image.
#
# Manim's Cairo backend needs cairo + pango headers to compile its
# Python bindings; ffmpeg is needed at runtime for any rasterizing
# scene (we don't rasterize on the server, but importing manim still
# probes for it). pkg-config wires the dev headers up for pip-build.
#
# We deliberately do NOT install texlive — our Manim subset
# (animation_extractor/manim_prompt.py SUBSET_RULES) forbids MathTex
# / Tex, so we skip the multi-GB TeX download.

ffmpeg
libcairo2-dev
libpango1.0-dev
pkg-config
fontconfig
